00:29:01,270 --> 00:29:03,864
You must carve out some time
everyday for rehearsing.

219
00:29:04,540 --> 00:29:09,273
Look at me... I must fetch Sonu
from school after I finish cooking.

220
00:29:09,612 --> 00:29:12,638
I'll go and fetch Sonu... Yes. l
will. It doesn't really matter.

221
00:29:18,587 --> 00:29:21,287
Will you please draw a bath for me?
Make it fast. I've to attend a party.

222
00:29:21,457 --> 00:29:24,688
- What party? - Oh, there's
something I'd like you to know.

223
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:28,418
- I've dumped the job.
- Why?

224
00:29:28,964 --> 00:29:33,196
l had enough of Mehra's abuses.
Besides, I want to move upwards.

225
00:29:33,903 --> 00:29:39,000
- What's more, I met Gulbadan
Kumar today. - Gulbadan Kumar?!

226
00:29:39,442 --> 00:29:42,673
Yes. He owns Prince Records. Its
really tough to get to meet him.

227
00:29:43,179 --> 00:29:47,343
I walked into his office and sang
a few songs. He liked my voice.

228
00:29:48,084 --> 00:29:53,317
He invited me to the party this
evening. Looks like I've made it.

229
00:29:54,056 --> 00:29:57,253
- Just press these clothes for me,
will you? - I'm coming with you!

230
00:29:57,560 --> 00:30:00,028
- What'll you do there? You'd get
bored. - No. I won't get bored.

231
00:30:00,863 --> 00:30:03,559
- What about Sonu?
- Farida can put him to sleep.

232
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:07,567
All right. You can come along.
Get dressed in some good clothes.

233
00:30:07,803 --> 00:30:09,737
Now. Take the clothes.
Press them quickly.

234
00:30:15,511 --> 00:30:18,446
Congratulations, Mr. Gulbadan Kumar.
Ever since your company was formed...

235
00:30:18,881 --> 00:30:23,318
-... music sales have grown manifold.
-It's the grace of The Divine Mother.

236
00:30:26,455 --> 00:30:29,982
A double gold disc for the music
directors. Someday I'll get mine too.

237
00:30:33,429 --> 00:30:36,489
l've recorded my voice on
a cassette... Rohit...!

238
00:30:36,966 --> 00:30:38,797
l've recorded one of
my songs in a cassette.

239
00:30:39,468 --> 00:30:44,337
- Will you please give it
to Gulbadan Kumar? - All right.

240
00:30:46,742 --> 00:30:51,202
Hows the good lady? I greet you
in the name of The Divine Mother.

241
00:30:52,114 --> 00:30:55,345
- Hello. - I'm Rohit Kumar.
- Of course, Mr. Rohit Kumar.

242
00:30:55,718 --> 00:30:57,811
- Greetings! - Grand party.
- It's modest really.

243
00:30:58,854 --> 00:31:02,756
- Have you listened to my cassette?
- Yes I did. - Did you like it?

244
00:31:03,993 --> 00:31:06,018
- Very nice.
- Thank you, Sir. Thank you, Sir.

245
00:31:10,399 --> 00:31:13,163
Glory be to The Divine Mother!

246
00:31:14,236 --> 00:31:17,330
Congratulations, Mr. Gulbadan!
You're raking in gold discs.

247
00:31:17,740 --> 00:31:19,105
Let's pose for a photograph.

248
00:31:21,710 --> 00:31:23,974
- You're the biggest of them all.
- Not at all. - lsn't it, now?

249
00:31:24,547 --> 00:31:30,315
It's the two of you, Messrs Amar &
Kaushik who are the most well known.

250
00:31:30,653 --> 00:31:35,488
That's the magic of our music.
We've defined 6 super hit films.

251
00:31:35,891 --> 00:31:38,587
- Our critics are now silenced.
- lndeed. lndeed, Mr. Gulbadan.

252
00:31:39,028 --> 00:31:41,963
You must listen to the music
we've scored for our next film.

253
00:31:42,231 --> 00:31:44,825
- The Divine Mother be praised. - We
recorded a song yesterday. Beautiful!

254
00:31:46,969 --> 00:31:48,163
Which film is the song meant for?

255
00:31:49,138 --> 00:31:52,938
Well... he's an upcoming artiste.
He's also a singer.

256
00:31:53,375 --> 00:31:56,139
- Mr. Rahul Kumar.
- I'm Rohit Kumar, Sir.

257
00:31:56,512 --> 00:31:57,843
Oh yes,... Mr. Rohit Kumar.

258
00:31:58,214 --> 00:31:59,681
- Do you sing?
- Yes, Sir.

259
00:32:00,683 --> 00:32:02,173
I see. For whom
have you sung till now?

260
00:32:02,885 --> 00:32:08,551
- Nothing special yet. - Yes. Go on.
- I want to sing for you.- Of course.

261
00:32:10,492 --> 00:32:13,592
- Don't forget to give my cassette.
- Oh yes. But, stop it now, will you?

262
00:32:13,629 --> 00:32:16,860
- Yes... what is it?
- I'm not only a singer.

263
00:32:17,666 --> 00:32:18,758
l've written a few songs too.

264
00:32:20,135 --> 00:32:22,467
- And what are you?!
- A composer.

265
00:32:23,806 --> 00:32:27,173
ln a country like ours, just
about anyone can turn a composer.

266
00:32:29,044 --> 00:32:34,607
Call me up on Monday. If your
voice is worth it, you're made.

267
00:32:36,552 --> 00:32:38,212
I'll come over on Monday
after giving you a call.

268
00:32:38,287 --> 00:32:40,149
What more could you want?
Glory be to The Divine Mother.

269
00:32:40,189 --> 00:32:41,652
- Mr. Gulbadan...
- Yes, Sir.

270
00:32:42,224 --> 00:32:43,919
Why aren't you giving
him my cassette?

271
00:32:44,393 --> 00:32:45,987
- I can't give the cassette now.
- Why?

272
00:32:46,028 --> 00:32:49,020
- It was so difficult getting an
audition for myself. - So what?

273
00:32:49,465 --> 00:32:51,729
How can I ask them to
audition my wife too?

274
00:32:52,101 --> 00:32:54,399
They'll think I'm trying to
force my family down their throats.

275
00:33:13,789 --> 00:33:18,488
- So, d'you feel that I'm imposing
myself upon you? - I never said that.

276
00:33:19,428 --> 00:33:23,592
- That's what you meant! - I'm tired
and I don't want to get into a fight.

277
00:33:23,766 --> 00:33:25,594
D'you mean to say that l
want to get into a fight?

278
00:33:25,768 --> 00:33:26,462
Sonu is sleeping.

279
00:33:27,369 --> 00:33:34,537
l'd only asked you to hand over
my cassette. Was it so difficult?

280
00:33:34,910 --> 00:33:40,212
I haven't heard what you've recorded.
I don't even know what's in it.

281
00:33:40,549 --> 00:33:43,518
I don't know if it's worth a hearing.
And, it was tough getting an audition.

282
00:33:43,886 --> 00:33:46,354
Must I lose a chance by trying
to push your cassette?

283
00:33:49,425 --> 00:33:53,452
An hour ago, you loved my voice.
Now, it isn't worth auditioning!

284
00:33:53,595 --> 00:33:56,189
I don't mean that. One must practice
regularly to be able to sing properly.

285
00:33:56,465 --> 00:34:00,834
Just another excuse! And I think l
understand you perfectly, Rohit.

286
00:34:00,970 --> 00:34:05,771
You've been pursuing your career.
And all I get are flimsy excuses.

287
00:34:06,709 --> 00:34:09,133
- Please don't scream.
- Why don't you say it plainly?

288
00:34:09,243 --> 00:34:14,478
That I don't have the aesthetics.
That I should stop dreaming about...

289
00:34:15,084 --> 00:34:17,514
...becoming a professional singer.
That's not what's going to be, Rohit.

290
00:34:17,886 --> 00:34:22,789
I won't give up! And you for one,
cannot break my resolve! Get that?

291
00:34:28,530 --> 00:34:32,933
I don't know why Rohit is doing
this. He mustn't do this to you.

292
00:34:33,369 --> 00:34:36,065
- It's wrong on his part. - We've
finished our homework, Mother.

293
00:34:36,405 --> 00:34:39,602
- May we go to play? - Make sure
you return soon. - All right.

294
00:34:44,313 --> 00:34:48,647
You have the right to a career.
Why don't you discuss it with Rohit?

295
00:34:54,156 --> 00:34:56,647
What are you doing here? I've been
looking for you so long.

296
00:34:57,526 --> 00:34:59,517
- I had to discuss some
things with Farida. - What?

297
00:34:59,995 --> 00:35:02,156
Besides Sonu is getting on my nerves.
Who is to take care of him?

298
00:35:02,631 --> 00:35:05,259
I have to go to a rehearsal. Where
are my clothes? How about some food?

299
00:35:06,168 --> 00:35:10,229
- I'm coming over. - And, where's
the file of my songs?

300
00:35:10,606 --> 00:35:13,234
l've been looking for it all day.
I just can't find it.

301
00:35:13,542 --> 00:35:15,339
l'd brought it down with me for my
practice session.

302
00:35:21,417 --> 00:35:24,545
Why don't you just sit over here for
the rest of the day practicing!

303
00:35:24,887 --> 00:35:27,014
- I said I'm coming. - Don't bother.
You can practice singing...

304
00:35:27,322 --> 00:35:29,980
...for the rest of the day.
I'll feed myself at a restaurant.

305
00:35:30,058 --> 00:35:32,591
- I'll look after the household too.
- Have I ever refused to do all that?

306
00:35:43,172 --> 00:35:46,505
- What've you done? - Sorry, Mother.
- You've got my washing all dirty.

307
00:35:47,409 --> 00:35:51,846
l've been at the laundry for 2 hours.
And I've asked you not to play here.

308
00:35:52,781 --> 00:35:56,080
How many times have l
asked you not to play?!

309
00:35:57,486 --> 00:36:00,455
What's up, Kiran? Why did you beat
him? What has he done?

310
00:36:00,923 --> 00:36:04,984
He won't listen to me. And now,
he's got the laundry all dirty.

311
00:36:06,361 --> 00:36:11,162
I'm sick and tired of chorus all day.
l've gone out of my mind.

312
00:36:22,778 --> 00:36:29,013
We tread upon the same path, Kiran.
What could be better for both of us?

313
00:37:15,764 --> 00:37:24,297
Open up, quickly.
Come on, hurry up.

314
00:37:26,942 --> 00:37:30,969
Make sure to remember the day today.
We'll celebrate this day every year.

315
00:37:31,380 --> 00:37:34,577
This is the day I've awaited forever.
The day on which my career commences!

316
00:37:35,117 --> 00:37:39,884
Today was the day! Amar-Kaushik were
left speechless after I auditioned.

317
00:37:40,222 --> 00:37:43,453
I'm singing the first song
for Pawan Chopra's new film.

318
00:37:44,226 --> 00:37:45,625
I'm leaving, Rohit.

319
00:37:46,295 --> 00:37:50,254
And they said that if this song
passes the muster while recording...

320
00:37:50,632 --> 00:37:53,829
...I'll get to sing all the songs
for the film. I'm recording tomorrow.

321
00:37:54,336 --> 00:37:56,099
- Want to come along?
- I said I'm leaving.

322
00:37:57,206 --> 00:37:59,231
- Where are you going?
- Here are the keys to the house.

323
00:37:59,808 --> 00:38:02,902
These are the rationing cards...and
here are the bills for the month.

324
00:38:03,278 --> 00:38:04,575
l've paid all the bills.

325
00:38:05,314 --> 00:38:07,612
You'll find the balance of the
money in the cupboard.

326
00:38:08,383 --> 00:38:12,820
Here's the electricity bill. Make
sure you pay it up by the weekend.

327
00:38:14,790 --> 00:38:16,917
I'm leaving you.

328
00:38:17,292 --> 00:38:19,886
Wait a minute! What are you saying?
What's happened?

329
00:38:20,262 --> 00:38:23,254
- Have I done anything wrong?
- No, you haven't. - What's it then?

330
00:38:23,632 --> 00:38:24,656
- Tell me.
- Don't touch me!

331
00:38:25,234 --> 00:38:27,930
- Just let me go. - But why are
you leaving? Say something!

332
00:38:28,237 --> 00:38:34,005
Why don't you understand! It isn't
just an isolated something.

333
00:38:35,010 --> 00:38:36,500
It might be my mistake too.

334
00:38:37,512 --> 00:38:41,346
- Something is happening to me.
- What's this with you?

335
00:38:42,517 --> 00:38:46,112
- I don't know! - It's nothing more
than a figment of your imagination.

336
00:38:50,259 --> 00:38:56,926
-I must make a life for myself. -But
this and here, is what your life is!

337
00:39:00,636 --> 00:39:02,866
Else, I'll go out of my mind.

338
00:39:05,507 --> 00:39:10,410
So you want to walk out of this
marriage. But what of Sonu?

339
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:12,941
How can you walk out on him?

340
00:39:15,784 --> 00:39:19,584
But, he's better off without me.

341
00:39:19,888 --> 00:39:23,756
Oh God! I don't believe this! Kiran!
Why are you doing this to me?!

342
00:39:24,593 --> 00:39:29,087
l've just got my golden chance. And
here you are...walking out on me!

343
00:39:29,765 --> 00:39:34,964
I need you, Kiran. If you stand by
me, I can even reach for the stars.

344
00:39:36,438 --> 00:39:38,906
But you had told me that we'd reach
out for the stars together.

345
00:39:43,712 --> 00:39:46,545
D'you feel that I'm trying to stop
you from becoming a singer?

346
00:39:47,082 --> 00:39:49,846
You might dream of becoming a singer.

347
00:39:50,319 --> 00:39:53,345
But don't expect me to go around
singing false praises for you.

348
00:39:56,858 --> 00:40:02,296
I lost my head. I agree that both
of us have made mistakes.

349
00:40:02,631 --> 00:40:05,124
But that doesn't mean that you must
walk out of your home. lsn't that so?

350
00:40:05,934 --> 00:40:09,097
We can always mend our ways.
Now, come in.

351
00:40:11,073 --> 00:40:12,734
Now you're being stubborn. Just
like your parents.

352
00:40:14,142 --> 00:40:17,407
-Don't drag my parents into this.
-Why not? You carry the same traits.

353
00:40:17,779 --> 00:40:19,474
Now, are you going to stop
taunting my parents?!

354
00:40:19,781 --> 00:40:22,045
Won't l! They haven't been able to
achieve anything in life.

355
00:40:22,384 --> 00:40:23,646
And they're jealous of others.

356
00:40:26,855 --> 00:40:29,824
- And d'you think I'm jealous of
your success? - Yes!

357
00:40:32,394 --> 00:40:35,386
Thank you very much.
I won't ever forget that.

358
00:40:36,264 --> 00:40:42,225
l'd rather suffer my traits than
your taunts for the rest of my life.

359
00:41:04,393 --> 00:41:06,987
Where has Kiran gone?

360
00:41:08,697 --> 00:41:11,666
- What I should be asking you?
- Why me?

361
00:41:12,100 --> 00:41:14,625
Because she used to spend more than
half her working hours in your company.

362
00:41:14,936 --> 00:41:18,804
And the two of you must've more than
discussed my weak points.

363
00:41:19,374 --> 00:41:22,172
Forget all that. Kiran has left you.

364
00:41:22,577 --> 00:41:25,137
- We must do something about it.
- Not ''we''. It's I who has to do.

365
00:41:25,214 --> 00:41:27,211
And I'll do whatever must be done.

366
00:41:27,549 --> 00:41:32,009
You must try to understand it now
or never. Kiran is very unhappy.

367
00:41:32,387 --> 00:41:34,946
- And the fact is that...
- Fact remains that of the past 6 years...

368
00:41:34,990 --> 00:41:36,758
... I've been trying heart and soul
to get a break...

369
00:41:37,058 --> 00:41:39,754
... so that my career can take off;
so that my life shapes up!

370
00:41:41,062 --> 00:41:43,895
After 6 long years, I get a break.
I'm slated to sing for Amar-Kaushik!

371
00:41:44,199 --> 00:41:47,030
I took a cab home as soon as I got
to know; so that I could...

372
00:41:47,168 --> 00:41:49,428
... share the greatest moment of
my life with her.

373
00:41:49,438 --> 00:41:52,036
And she tells me that she's
walking out of my life.

374
00:41:52,641 --> 00:41:58,170
- What does it mean?! - She couldn't
share the greatest moment of your life.

375
00:41:58,346 --> 00:42:03,909
- It's your life, after all.
- You're fantastic!

376
00:42:05,487 --> 00:42:09,014
That your husband deserted you
because you were unhappy...

377
00:42:09,324 --> 00:42:12,487
... doesn't mean that every woman
is unhappy with her husband.

378
00:42:17,566 --> 00:42:21,297
I haven't come here to discuss my
husband. I'm concerned about Kiran.

379
00:42:22,003 --> 00:42:24,904
- You may keep your concern within
your confines. - I shall.

380
00:42:25,407 --> 00:42:29,207
Before I leave, let me tell you that
you could never understand Kiran.

381
00:42:29,711 --> 00:42:32,475
She is no petty woman to serve as
a part of your interior decor.

382
00:42:32,814 --> 00:42:36,773
She had her own dreams. And it
takes courage for a woman to walk out.

383
00:42:37,886 --> 00:42:44,587
Yes! And it takes more to walk out
on a helpless child. lsn't that so?

384
00:43:20,662 --> 00:43:29,502
- Why are you sleeping here?
- Oh.. what? - And where's Mummy?

385
00:43:33,842 --> 00:43:36,538
- Tell me... Where's Mummy?
- What's the time now?

386
00:43:38,046 --> 00:43:40,776
The small hand is on 7.
And the big hand is on 3.

387
00:43:42,150 --> 00:43:44,914
I'm going to be late
for the recording.

388
00:43:45,353 --> 00:43:49,449
- Tell me, Daddy... where's Mummy?
- Wait a minute.

389
00:43:52,694 --> 00:43:57,495
- You mother has gone to your aunt's.
- Which aunt?

390
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:03,937
-The one in Pune. -Aunt Ratna lives
there. - That's where she has gone.

391
00:44:04,806 --> 00:44:09,937
- When is she going to come back?
- Very soon.. in 3 or 4 days.

392
00:44:10,378 --> 00:44:13,643
Now make a move.
l've got to get ready.

393
00:44:15,317 --> 00:44:18,809
- Who's going to get me ready
for school? - I will, son.

394
00:44:20,388 --> 00:44:22,481
- And, who'll pack my school bag?
- I will.

395
00:44:24,926 --> 00:44:28,225
- Who'll take me to school?
- I will.

396
00:44:28,530 --> 00:44:33,467
- What about my breakfast? - l...
what do you eat for breakfast?

397
00:44:33,902 --> 00:44:37,338
An omelette of 2 eggs, toast with
butter and Bournvita.

398
00:44:42,677 --> 00:44:46,807
A dash of coriander... and onions.
Ever had one of my omelets?

399
00:44:47,148 --> 00:44:51,710
- No.
- Try it today. You'll love it.

400
00:44:54,155 --> 00:44:58,148
- You're cutting them in such
large chunks! - That's just fine.

401
00:44:59,761 --> 00:45:01,592
lsn't this fun! Yes, it's fun.

402
00:45:02,631 --> 00:45:07,625
Now, take a look at this.. a circus
with one hand... two eggs in one hand!

403
00:45:07,969 --> 00:45:10,267
Now take a look at how I break
both eggs using one hand.

404
00:45:13,608 --> 00:45:16,702
The eggs had soft-shells.
But never mind.

405
00:45:20,382 --> 00:45:22,407
This place is perfectly clean.

406
00:45:23,818 --> 00:45:27,515
What are you doing?
I'm not going to eat that!

407
00:45:27,956 --> 00:45:31,892
- It has shells in it. - A few
shells will make the omelette crisp.

408
00:45:32,560 --> 00:45:35,028
- Here go the onions... and the
chilies. - Not that way! - How else?

409
00:45:35,497 --> 00:45:39,126
Mummy used to flip the
ingredients first.

410
00:45:39,634 --> 00:45:43,161
What Mummy doesn't know is that an
omelette is an omelette, flip or flap!

411
00:45:44,172 --> 00:45:47,630
Eat it and you'll know. Later on,
I'll drop you at the school.

412
00:45:47,909 --> 00:45:50,878
And afterwards, I'm off to record
my first song ever!

413
00:45:51,346 --> 00:45:54,440
Your Daddy is going to
become a famous singer.

414
00:45:55,850 --> 00:45:58,341
- What's up?
- The toast is burning!

415
00:45:59,788 --> 00:46:02,188
Well, never mind that.

416
00:46:14,536 --> 00:46:15,935
You don't know a thing!

417
00:46:18,173 --> 00:46:22,507
Go on in... hurry.
Go inside.

418
00:46:23,411 --> 00:46:25,345
- Who'll come to pick me up?
- I'll come.

419
00:46:26,047 --> 00:46:27,344
Where are you going to
wait for me?

420
00:46:28,917 --> 00:46:31,511
I'll wait for you under this tree,
okay? Now go on inside.

421
00:46:32,287 --> 00:46:35,256
- What if you don't turn up?
- I said I'll come. And, I will.

422
00:46:35,924 --> 00:46:39,758
- What if you're late? - I won't
be late. I'll be here on time.

423
00:46:40,261 --> 00:46:47,565
- What if you're still late? - If
I am, you can wait under the tree.

424
00:46:48,870 --> 00:46:50,337
Go on, now. Hurry.

425
00:46:52,440 --> 00:46:56,171
- When does the school get over?
- No idea.

426
00:46:59,681 --> 00:47:02,479
When does the junior school
get over?

427
