He asked me why I went to see
a film when he was sick.

647
01:11:41,361 --> 01:11:45,092
I couldn't bore myself sitting
by him all evening; now could l?

648
01:11:45,565 --> 01:11:47,089
Have I done anything wrong?

649
01:11:49,002 --> 01:11:51,562
Tell me, Anjali... have
I done anything wrong?

650
01:11:55,375 --> 01:11:56,865
You were supposed to
deliver your lines.

651
01:11:57,644 --> 01:11:58,872
Don't you remember your lines?

652
01:12:03,183 --> 01:12:04,707
Will she be able to
deliver the lines?

653
01:12:05,318 --> 01:12:10,722
You wanted someone simple and
innocent. She'll deliver all right.

654
01:12:11,725 --> 01:12:13,693
Didn't I tell you that I don't
know anything about acting?

655
01:12:17,731 --> 01:12:19,392
All you have to do
is to my your lines.

656
01:12:24,070 --> 01:12:26,038
Tell me, Anjali...
What have I done wrong?

657
01:12:28,375 --> 01:12:31,902
You haven't done
the right thing, Deepa.

658
01:12:34,648 --> 01:12:38,379
D'you remember how anxious he
was when you had fallen sick?

659
01:12:38,752 --> 01:12:43,052
He kept by you and cared
for you like a man possessed.

660
01:12:43,957 --> 01:12:48,690
And you can't even spare
an evening for him!

661
01:12:49,262 --> 01:12:50,991
You call that boredom.

662
01:12:52,299 --> 01:12:56,963
The truth is that you've
never even understood Sunju.

663
01:12:58,004 --> 01:12:59,767
He loves you very much.

664
01:13:03,376 --> 01:13:06,243
She's going on saying
whatever she wants to.

665
01:13:11,384 --> 01:13:13,545
l'd told you earlier that l
know nothing about acting.

666
01:13:14,187 --> 01:13:21,252
I tried it at my friend's instance.
I really want to become a singer.

667
01:13:22,329 --> 01:13:27,858
- Very well... you may sing some.
- Sir...?!

668
01:14:23,323 --> 01:14:25,985
- Please listen to the songs I've
scored. - I've helped you already.

669
01:14:26,426 --> 01:14:29,623
I introduced you to Amar Kaushik.
And you've disgraced me.

670
01:14:30,196 --> 01:14:33,962
- They started misbehaving with me.
- Will they really misbehave?

671
01:14:35,368 --> 01:14:38,462
- You see, Mr.Gulbadan. - You see,
Mr. Rohit, I merely run...

672
01:14:38,705 --> 01:14:41,538
.. a small-time music company. We
only publish records and cassettes.

673
01:14:41,975 --> 01:14:47,971
I'm not a film producer.
Now, please excuse me.

674
01:14:51,785 --> 01:14:54,583
- I'll be back in a minute.
- Please take your time.

675
01:14:55,355 --> 01:14:57,721
One minute, Mr. Rohit.

676
01:14:58,525 --> 01:15:00,049
I can help you sell your songs.

677
01:15:00,660 --> 01:15:05,620
Amar Kaushik needs new tunes.
I'll get you 2000 for each tune.

678
01:15:05,999 --> 01:15:08,934
- Here's my card. - So they get
the credit for my compositions.

679
01:15:09,369 --> 01:15:10,495
Why bother about the credit?

680
01:15:22,549 --> 01:15:26,212
You want me to give you a job so
you can walk out on me again.

681
01:15:27,053 --> 01:15:32,548
That won't happen ever again. I beg
your pardon. Please give me a chance.

682
01:16:11,231 --> 01:16:14,223
- lsn't that, Mrs. Kiran?
- Yes. She's Rohit Kumar's wife.

683
01:16:14,601 --> 01:16:16,796
- She's made a heroine in films.
- She used to sing.

684
01:16:17,270 --> 01:16:19,329
And now, she's up to
dancing in public.

685
01:16:19,873 --> 01:16:23,934
Come quickly, Dad.
Take a look... over there.

686
01:16:24,244 --> 01:16:25,836
It's Mummy's picture.

687
01:16:27,280 --> 01:16:28,838
They put up the posters today.

688
01:16:30,750 --> 01:16:35,449
I want to see Mummy's film. You'll
take me to see it, won't you?

689
01:16:35,955 --> 01:16:40,858
You'll take me, won't you, Daddy?...
Won't you, Daddy? Please tell me.

690
01:17:46,369 --> 01:17:47,961
How are we to see Mummy's film now?

691
01:17:50,373 --> 01:17:52,500
It's a ''house-full'' show.
Let's go home.

692
01:17:53,143 --> 01:17:58,945
I want to see Mummy's film! You'd
promised to show me Mummy's film.

693
01:18:00,116 --> 01:18:02,744
I want to see Mummy's film at once!

694
01:18:10,760 --> 01:18:11,658
Hurry up, Daddy.

695
01:18:33,883 --> 01:18:36,408
How come you're here?
No one is allowed up here.

696
01:18:36,853 --> 01:18:40,619
He wants to see how his Mummy's film
is projected. I spoke to the manager.

697
01:18:41,357 --> 01:18:44,520
-ls he Ms. Kiran's son? -Yes. -Very
well. You can sit here and see it.

698
01:18:45,662 --> 01:18:47,493
''Tell me... what can
you do for my sake''

699
01:18:48,164 --> 01:18:50,928
''I can do just about
anything for your sake.''

700
01:18:51,367 --> 01:18:53,858
''I'd get the sun, the moon
and the stars for you.''

701
01:18:54,270 --> 01:18:58,172
''I'd bring the heavens and
earth together for your sake.''

702
01:19:00,477 --> 01:19:04,277
- What's the matter, honey? - I'd
rather love a straightforward fellow.

703
01:19:04,714 --> 01:19:06,875
''You needn't bring the sun, moon,
nor the stars into this.''

704
01:19:23,800 --> 01:19:25,995
''You can take your rotten son back
to America with you.''

705
01:19:26,336 --> 01:19:28,395
'' Before you leave, try some
delicious lndian cakes.''

706
01:20:21,191 --> 01:20:23,290
Can you tell us how you are feeling
right now, Mrs. Kiran?

707
01:20:23,293 --> 01:20:25,485
I'm happy to see that the audiences
have liked my performance.

708
01:20:25,695 --> 01:20:28,163
- Would you like to work again with
Paresh Kapoor? - Yes, of course.

709
01:20:28,598 --> 01:20:30,828
Any plans for the future?
What kind of films would you like?

710
01:20:31,668 --> 01:20:36,264
- I haven't thought about it. - We
hear that you are Mrs. Kiran Kumar.

711
01:20:36,706 --> 01:20:39,470
- It's said that you're married, and
that you have a son. Who said that?

712
01:20:40,143 --> 01:20:44,011
Don't ask vulgar questions. And now
you've had enough. Please step aside.

713
01:20:45,381 --> 01:20:47,042
Come along, Kiran. Let's go.

714
01:21:30,760 --> 01:21:36,062
- Has Mummy forgotten me, Daddy?
- No.- Then why didn't she stop?

715
01:21:36,532 --> 01:21:37,863
Why didn't she talk to me?

716
01:21:40,737 --> 01:21:44,935
- Can I go to see her sometime?
- No. - Why not?

717
01:21:53,716 --> 01:21:55,445
Did you see those stars?

718
01:21:57,086 --> 01:22:00,146
They shine, merrily, but they are
far away from us.

719
01:22:01,090 --> 01:22:07,689
Your Mummy is now like a star. You
can see her and long for her.

720
01:22:08,398 --> 01:22:10,559
But you can't go anywhere near her.

721
01:22:19,025 --> 01:22:21,289
Come on...Let's go home.

722
01:22:38,744 --> 01:22:40,735
Then, my Mummy goes to a forest.

723
01:22:41,214 --> 01:22:43,273
She comes across a
huge fellow in the forest.

724
01:22:43,950 --> 01:22:47,579
My Mummy bashes him up.

725
01:22:48,621 --> 01:22:51,112
- Go upstairs, Sunil.
- After a minute, please, Daddy.

726
01:22:51,657 --> 01:22:55,991
Then the hero comes, and sings a
song with my Mummy.

727
01:22:56,596 --> 01:23:01,260
-My mummy's very beautiful.-Really?
-She's more beautiful than yours.

728
01:23:03,402 --> 01:23:08,169
Beautiful she is. But, she's more
stubborn than she's beautiful.

729
01:23:08,641 --> 01:23:12,304
Why don't you go over to her, patch
up and bring her back?

730
01:23:13,746 --> 01:23:22,484
If I go to her now, she'll think
that I've come because she's a star.

731
01:23:22,855 --> 01:23:29,727
Forget her. ln any case, it was she
who left me. I didn't desert her.

732
01:23:30,897 --> 01:23:35,357
- She can return if she wants to.
- And you're very stubborn too.

733
01:23:38,471 --> 01:23:42,100
We've finished the cola.
Hey Moolchand!

734
01:23:44,577 --> 01:23:48,111
- What's up? - 2 Colas please.
- I've closed for the day.

735
01:23:48,148 --> 01:23:49,105
Down the shutter.

736
01:23:50,550 --> 01:23:54,077
-Open up if you've closed down. - Am
I to stay open all night for you?

737
01:23:55,021 --> 01:23:57,489
If you're so interested, you could
walk a block to fetch it.

738
01:23:58,391 --> 01:24:01,554
- Why don't you fetch some for us?
- Am I your servant?

739
01:24:02,395 --> 01:24:07,765
- Forget him. He's an illiterate.
- What?! An illiterate, am l?!

740
01:24:08,101 --> 01:24:09,490
Did you call me an illiterate?

741
01:24:09,669 --> 01:24:13,605
Oh yes. I am an illiterate. And l
know exactly what I am. Unlike you.

742
01:24:14,073 --> 01:24:16,974
You sing in a rotten nightclubs and
think you're no less than Elvis.

743
01:24:17,710 --> 01:24:21,305
He calls me an illiterate! And he
sits drinking in front of his son.

744
01:24:21,781 --> 01:24:25,979
You couldn't even take care of your
wife. And he is lording it over me!

745
01:24:26,719 --> 01:24:28,516
You bloody! What
did you say about my wife?!

746
01:24:28,988 --> 01:24:31,456
- No! Don't!
- What did you say about my wife?!

747
01:24:31,691 --> 01:24:33,181
I'll break your face! I will!

748
01:24:34,226 --> 01:24:39,459
- Let go! And you! Get lost!
- Don't you dare touch me!- Get lost?

749
01:24:40,499 --> 01:24:45,436
- Let's go! Just come back here...
and I'll show you! - Don't fight!

750
01:24:46,472 --> 01:24:48,633
Go home, Moolchand!

751
01:24:49,241 --> 01:24:52,438
And you're a strange fellow. Must
you pick up a fight with such a scum?

752
01:24:52,979 --> 01:24:57,211
- Bad fellow! Come on, let's have
a drink. - No, he spoilt my mood.

753
01:24:57,817 --> 01:24:58,749
Come home, Sunil.

754
01:25:04,523 --> 01:25:05,785
What's it with you, now?

755
01:25:12,898 --> 01:25:16,356
Hey! I just fell down.
Let's squat here for sometime.

756
01:25:18,671 --> 01:25:25,133
- Why do you drink rum, Daddy?
- What did you know about rum?

757
01:25:25,811 --> 01:25:27,870
I know everything.
Rum is an alcoholic drink.

758
01:25:30,683 --> 01:25:34,210
One day, a drunk came
to the gates of our school.

759
01:25:34,687 --> 01:25:38,521
The kids at school were
teasing him and poking fun at him.

760
01:25:38,591 --> 01:25:40,049
And everyone threw stones at him.

761
01:25:40,092 --> 01:25:43,625
I don't want anyone
to make fun of you.

762
01:25:48,534 --> 01:25:49,831
Do you love me so much?

763
01:25:53,439 --> 01:25:59,867
I love you very much too. I love
you more than anyone else on earth.

764
01:26:00,179 --> 01:26:02,909
If you love me so much,
you must stop drinking.

765
01:26:04,050 --> 01:26:09,386
From now on, I won't drink.

766
01:26:22,601 --> 01:26:26,503
There's this fatso in our class.
Deven. He bullies everyone around.

767
01:26:26,872 --> 01:26:31,741
He snatched Prakash's lunch box
away. I complained to the teacher.

768
01:26:32,144 --> 01:26:35,170
Why complain? Box him in the
stomach. That'll do him right.

769
01:26:35,648 --> 01:26:38,242
- Well, what will you do to him?
- I'll box him in the stomach.

770
01:26:50,062 --> 01:26:51,927
Go on now.
I'll be back to take you home.

771
01:27:10,883 --> 01:27:14,478
I was passing by when
I saw the two of you.

772
01:27:17,690 --> 01:27:19,521
Sonu was looking quite cheerful.

773
01:27:21,694 --> 01:27:31,330
I'd thought I'd
call you up sometime.

774
01:27:32,905 --> 01:27:36,102
But I decided that it'd be better
if I met you personally.

775
01:27:42,214 --> 01:27:43,078
How are you?

776
01:27:45,351 --> 01:27:50,618
I'm fine, and I don't have much
to worry about. How have you been?

777
01:28:43,809 --> 01:28:48,644
- Are you very forlorn, Daddy?
- No, I'm not. Why do you ask?

778
01:28:49,415 --> 01:28:52,748
Nothing particularly. Are you
thinking about Mummy?

779
01:28:55,921 --> 01:28:57,320
Go to sleep now.

780
01:29:07,060 --> 01:29:12,960
<i>My heart says, go, meet her!</i>

781
