787
01:30:02,768 --> 01:30:08,669
<i>Sometimes I try to control it.</i>

788
01:30:45,769 --> 01:30:55,668
<i>My beloved, since
we have separated,</i>

789
01:30:57,769 --> 01:31:08,670
<i>I have everything with
me in my life.</i>

790
01:31:10,270 --> 01:31:15,170
<i>A lot of wealth...</i>

791
01:31:16,270 --> 01:31:20,170
<i>A lot of fame.</i>

792
01:31:21,270 --> 01:31:26,170
<i>But after losing you I feel that...</i>

793
01:31:27,270 --> 01:31:33,160
<i>I don't have anything
if you're not here.</i>

794
01:31:34,767 --> 01:31:39,665
<i>You don't know how many...</i>

795
01:31:39,766 --> 01:31:45,666
<i>regrets I have in my heart.</i>

796
01:31:46,260 --> 01:31:51,160
<i>Sometimes my heart
gets the better of me...</i>

797
01:31:52,270 --> 01:31:58,160
<i>Sometimes I try to control it.</i>

798
01:32:50,769 --> 01:32:55,668
<i>How beautiful were those days...</i>

799
01:32:56,769 --> 01:33:01,667
<i>when we were together.</i>

800
01:33:02,768 --> 01:33:13,664
<i>And I could embrace you.</i>

801
01:33:14,765 --> 01:33:25,660
<i>It was just you in
my days and nights...</i>

802
01:33:26,260 --> 01:33:31,160
<i>But you are so far
above me, my beloved...</i>

803
01:33:32,260 --> 01:33:37,160
<i>That I can't even touch you.</i>

804
01:33:38,260 --> 01:33:44,320
<i>It's impossible to reach you.</i>

805
01:33:44,768 --> 01:33:50,666
<i>Just thinking about it
makes me so miserable.</i>

806
01:33:51,260 --> 01:33:56,160
<i>Sometimes my heart
gets the better of me...</i>

807
01:33:57,260 --> 01:34:02,160
<i>Sometimes I try to control it.</i>

808
01:34:03,260 --> 01:34:08,160
<i>My heart says, go, meet him!</i>

809
01:34:09,260 --> 01:34:14,160
<i>But my feet stop as
they start to move forward.</i>

810
01:34:40,799 --> 01:34:43,768
- Take a look at this!
- What's up? - Read it!

811
01:34:44,169 --> 01:34:47,002
- Read..? -Read it..see who
wrote it! - One Pawan Malhotra.

812
01:34:47,306 --> 01:34:50,571
- The film director! - Didn't he
direct CHAHAT?-That's him all right!

813
01:34:50,976 --> 01:34:53,103
He has signed me up to score the
music for his forthcoming film.

814
01:34:53,478 --> 01:34:56,140
- What are saying?! - Really?!
- Yes! And I can't believe it!

815
01:34:56,515 --> 01:34:59,109
Pawan Malhotra patted
my shoulder and said...

816
01:34:59,585 --> 01:35:01,985
''You're a very talented fellow!
How come I didn't meet you before?''

817
01:35:02,321 --> 01:35:03,515
He liked my songs very much!

818
01:35:04,590 --> 01:35:06,990
Thank God for that.
And congratulations!

819
01:35:07,492 --> 01:35:08,390
Hey Moolchand!

820
01:35:09,695 --> 01:35:11,720
Take a look at this!
Get that?!

821
01:35:12,097 --> 01:35:13,155
All right. Understood.

822
01:35:15,167 --> 01:35:17,965
So you've got money!
When are you going to pay me up?

823
01:35:18,370 --> 01:35:20,861
I haven't yet received money.
I've just signed the contract.

824
01:35:21,273 --> 01:35:24,265
I'll get the money soon. Let's
celebrate with tea for everyone.

825
01:35:24,543 --> 01:35:26,841
- Very well..er..What do you mean?
- It's on me, of course.

826
01:35:27,313 --> 01:35:29,505
-You should've said so. Come on in.
-I'll have a cup of tea too!

827
01:35:34,353 --> 01:35:37,083
Are you going to become the
greatest music director now?

828
01:35:37,489 --> 01:35:40,215
That I'll become. But, do you know
what I'm going to do before that?

829
01:35:40,292 --> 01:35:42,189
- What? - Your birthday is coming up,
isn't it. - Oh yes.

830
01:35:42,229 --> 01:35:45,155
- I'll get you a surprise gift
for your birthday. - Really?

831
01:35:45,231 --> 01:35:49,059
- Yes. - What's it going to be?
- How can I tell you about it now?

832
01:35:49,301 --> 01:35:51,496
I know what! lsn't it something
I showed you the other day?

833
01:35:53,372 --> 01:35:54,600
ls it yellow in color?

834
01:35:55,440 --> 01:35:56,566
The battery operated car!

835
01:36:03,081 --> 01:36:07,211
- Where does Mr. Rohit Kumar live?
- I'm Rohit Kumar.

836
01:36:13,191 --> 01:36:15,125
Ms. Kiran has sent this for you.

837
01:36:15,527 --> 01:36:16,516
It's Mummy's car!

838
01:36:17,029 --> 01:36:20,829
Hey folks! Come on quick! Take a
look at this. It's my Mummy's car!

839
01:36:35,213 --> 01:36:36,077
What's it?

840
01:36:37,816 --> 01:36:38,882
It's a letter from Kiran.

841
01:36:40,819 --> 01:36:44,812
She wants to celebrate Sonu's
birthday. She has invited us over.

842
01:36:47,159 --> 01:36:49,627
You'll go over, won't you?

843
01:36:54,166 --> 01:36:55,531
You should go over.

844
01:37:01,273 --> 01:37:04,640
Tell her that we will come.
But, there's no need to sent the car.

845
01:37:27,766 --> 01:37:28,858
You mustn't be naughty, Sonu.

846
01:37:30,035 --> 01:37:32,027
And you must speak to everyone
politely, understand?

847
01:37:32,838 --> 01:37:34,430
- Are you listening to me?
- Yes. Okay.

848
01:37:35,607 --> 01:37:37,575
If anyone offers you anything
to eat, don't be greedy.

849
01:37:38,410 --> 01:37:41,641
Refuse it politely. But if you
must have it, say thanks afterwards.

850
01:37:42,013 --> 01:37:42,604
Sonu has arrived.

851
01:38:08,173 --> 01:38:11,631
- I hope we aren't late.
- No problem.

852
01:38:12,544 --> 01:38:16,241
- I was worried that you wouldn't
come. - But, I have come.

853
01:39:11,904 --> 01:39:15,330
Let me introduce you... my wife,
Lajwanti...and,...Mrs. Tolaram.

854
01:39:29,488 --> 01:39:33,754
- Sorry for leaving you alone for a
while. - Only a while, wasn't it?

855
01:39:37,062 --> 01:39:40,998
- I get childish when I'm with kids.
- You've always been childish.

856
01:39:45,370 --> 01:39:48,396
Sonu is still cheating at
the game. He's just like you!

857
01:39:52,410 --> 01:39:53,172
You're looking lovely.

858
01:39:57,182 --> 01:39:58,706
Come over here for a moment, Kiran.

859
01:39:59,551 --> 01:40:01,519
I'll be back in a moment.

860
01:40:04,589 --> 01:40:08,184
Won't you meet others around?
We have other guests too.

861
01:40:08,994 --> 01:40:11,827
Have you invited everyone to watch
you prancing with that fellow?

862
01:40:12,597 --> 01:40:16,590
-I'll leave this party if you speak
so. - You must consider your status.

863
01:40:17,168 --> 01:40:23,073
- You're a star. And, journalists
are attending. - Who invited them?

864
01:40:23,808 --> 01:40:27,676
I wanted to celebrate a birthday.
You've made a circus out of it.

865
01:40:28,280 --> 01:40:31,078
Don't teach me what to do
and what not to.

866
01:40:31,516 --> 01:40:37,455
As of now, just stay away from him.
We have other guests here too.

867
01:40:38,623 --> 01:40:41,217
- Happy tidings, Mr. Ramdayal.
- Thank you.

868
01:40:42,327 --> 01:40:43,760
Happy tidings to you too.

869
01:40:50,669 --> 01:40:55,936
- What's up? Any problem?
- Nothing at all.

870
01:40:57,742 --> 01:40:59,573
They might not have taken
a liking to my presence.

871
01:41:03,982 --> 01:41:09,045
- I should've sent Sonu here alone.
- But why? I wanted you to come too.

872
01:41:09,521 --> 01:41:11,989
I wanted all of us to celebrate
Sonu's birthday together.

873
01:41:12,958 --> 01:41:16,291
I've taken a lot of pains to organize
this party. And now, these people...

874
01:41:16,728 --> 01:41:20,095
... they've spoilt my mood.

875
01:41:29,207 --> 01:41:33,701
- I've asked you not to run around!
- Hey fatso! You won't catch me!

876
01:41:34,279 --> 01:41:37,774
- Let me go! He'll catch me! Let him.
- I got caught because of you!

877
01:41:37,783 --> 01:41:40,146
That's just as well. Now you can
sit with Mummy for a while.

878
01:41:41,886 --> 01:41:42,443
My child!

879
01:41:44,356 --> 01:41:48,292
- What's that mark? - I was playing
on the side. And I fell down.

880
01:41:49,060 --> 01:41:54,020
-Oh no! -And it bled a lot. -Did
it take stitches? - Yes 8 stitches.

881
01:41:54,866 --> 01:42:01,328
- How did it happen? - My mistake. l
wasn't careful. And he didn't listen.

882
01:42:02,507 --> 01:42:05,237
It didn't hurt his eyes, thank God!
I could never have forgiven myself.

883
01:42:05,910 --> 01:42:08,003
- And I didn't even cry.
- Really?

884
01:42:10,882 --> 01:42:13,009
- Come on, Mummy. I want to see
your house. - Let's go.

885
01:42:13,451 --> 01:42:16,147
- Come along too, will you?
- No. Just go on. - All right.

886
01:42:23,294 --> 01:42:25,023
- See you later.
- Excuse us.

887
01:42:28,166 --> 01:42:29,428
- Greetings.
- Greetings.

888
01:42:30,802 --> 01:42:34,636
- Have you had the cakes and other
goodies? - Yes I have, thank you.

889
01:42:35,874 --> 01:42:38,308
- Had enough?
- Not yet. I'll have some more.

890
01:42:43,615 --> 01:42:48,211
- Seen the villa?
- Yes. It's a huge one.

891
01:42:48,620 --> 01:42:52,818
-It stretches right up to the beach.
-There's a swimming pool back there.

892
01:42:53,224 --> 01:42:56,660
- I see! - It cost a million bucks.
- Fantastic.

893
01:42:59,097 --> 01:43:04,592
- Are you still at song-and-dance
at the hotel? - Well, you see...

894
01:43:05,036 --> 01:43:08,070
- Glory be to The Divine mother.
- Greetings, Mr.Gulbadan Kumar.

895
01:43:08,074 --> 01:43:10,832
Greetings. Happy tidings
on your son's birthday.

896
01:43:11,109 --> 01:43:15,944
I'm very upset with him, I am!
Tell me, is this any way to behave?!

897
01:43:16,347 --> 01:43:22,115
You're the sole object of discussion
in the film business nowadays.

898
01:43:22,620 --> 01:43:28,081
He has scored such lovely songs; and
he has put Amar Kaushik to shame!

899
01:43:29,327 --> 01:43:31,227
Well, you've become
a very important person nowadays.

900
01:43:31,663 --> 01:43:34,826
But you mustn't forget simple folks
like me. Do call up once in a while.

901
01:43:35,166 --> 01:43:37,896
- Never mind that. But you must
get me the music rights. - Sure.

902
01:43:39,037 --> 01:43:41,631
- Together, we'll make a stupendous
success out of it. - Surely.

903
01:43:42,774 --> 01:43:49,145
Divine Mother be praised! A heroine
and a music director in the family!

904
01:43:49,547 --> 01:43:54,075
No dearth of money! I suggest you
become a film producer. Say what?!

905
01:43:55,620 --> 01:43:58,521
- Excuse me. - Oh yes.
- Be back soon.

906
01:43:59,891 --> 01:44:03,156
- How many films have you signed?
- Just one till now.

907
01:44:04,696 --> 01:44:08,427
You'll get many more, I'm sure.
But take care about signing films.

908
01:44:08,833 --> 01:44:14,032
- What'd you like to have? Whisky
or rum? - I've stopped drinking.

909
01:44:14,839 --> 01:44:19,799
May The Divine Mother bless you!
A Coca-cola for the gentleman, please.

910
01:44:20,512 --> 01:44:23,811
Hello there! Nowadays, you don't
seem to care for us.

911
01:44:24,215 --> 01:44:27,844
That isn't the case at all.
ln fact, we were discussing you.

912
01:44:28,586 --> 01:44:32,022
After all, he has rising star with
him. Mr. Rohit Kumar!

913
01:44:32,891 --> 01:44:35,121
The singer and composer.
A two-in-one!

914
01:44:37,395 --> 01:44:44,699
Congratulations!
So even you've got a film!

915
01:44:46,070 --> 01:44:49,938
What I don't understand is how he
bagged the film.

916
01:44:50,375 --> 01:44:57,747
Because there still are people
who value caliber. Not names.

917
01:44:58,249 --> 01:45:03,084
I see! But I think that behind
every successful man lies a woman.

918
01:45:03,421 --> 01:45:08,552
But slightly different in this case;
..a successful woman behind the man!

919
01:45:11,095 --> 01:45:15,122
- What do you mean? - Can a woman
who is beautiful and successful...

920
01:45:15,466 --> 01:45:20,529
- ...not do as much for her husband?
- Surely she can do!

921
01:45:22,006 --> 01:45:26,272
- What nonsense are you speaking?
- Do you think Pawan Malhotra has...

922
01:45:26,644 --> 01:45:28,339
... signed you because he
likes your rotten songs?

923
01:45:28,713 --> 01:45:35,346
- We were supposed to sign this film.
- You've got it because of your wife.

924
01:45:36,187 --> 01:45:42,353
Don't believe it, d'you? Why! It's
commonplace. Come here, Mr. Tolaram.

925
01:45:42,660 --> 01:45:45,288
- Come here, Mr. Tolaram. - Yes.
Come here. - What's up, gentlemen?

926
01:45:45,530 --> 01:45:47,964
- Tell him... go on! Tell him how he
has landed this film. - Oh forget it!

927
01:45:48,366 --> 01:45:53,463
- Go on, speak up. Tell him! - He
has scored some very good songs.

928
01:45:53,805 --> 01:45:57,036
- To hell with the songs! You had
signed us. - Well yes, I did...

929
01:45:57,609 --> 01:46:02,979
- On his wife's say-so, you threw us
out! Correct? - Nothing of the sort!

930
01:46:03,381 --> 01:46:07,147
- She had merely...
- D'you hear that, Mister two-in-one?

931
01:46:07,418 --> 01:46:11,752
It happens dear. Everything goes
in this business.

932
01:46:12,357 --> 01:46:16,157
- People do use their good-looking
wives too. - Oh yes. They do.

933
01:46:23,701 --> 01:46:28,434
Look...look at what's going on
over there. Go on... over there.

934
01:46:32,210 --> 01:46:35,270
Someone bashes me up... and you're
trying to patch up! What's going on?

935
01:46:36,047 --> 01:46:40,780
That's true! He couldn't cook
anything. Not even eggs!

936
01:46:40,853 --> 01:46:44,084
Really?! How is it now? Nowadays
he has picked up a few things.

937
01:46:44,123 --> 01:46:46,815
He makes a dish out of potatoes
now and then. Of potatoes?! Yes.

938
01:46:47,458 --> 01:46:51,451
Sometimes, there are excess of
turmeric in it. But, I make do.

939
01:46:52,530 --> 01:46:53,997
Oh hello, Rohit. Come in.

940
01:46:54,632 --> 01:46:57,533
- Go downstairs, Sunil. - One minute
please, daddy, I want to tell mummy...

941
01:46:57,802 --> 01:47:01,738
- I asked you to go downstairs!
- What's up, Rohit?

942
01:47:04,943 --> 01:47:06,274
Wait for me downstairs.

943
01:47:10,581 --> 01:47:12,515
Did you speak to Pawan Malhotra
about me?

944
01:47:14,252 --> 01:47:16,686
Did you ask him to replace me with
Amar Kaushik as a music director?

945
01:47:18,056 --> 01:47:20,581
- Why are you asking me this?
- Did you tell him, or, didn't you?

946
01:47:22,694 --> 01:47:24,389
Give me an answer, Kiran.

947
01:47:26,597 --> 01:47:27,393
Yes.

948
01:47:28,466 --> 01:47:34,029
- Why?
- Because I wanted to help you.

949
01:47:34,572 --> 01:47:37,234
I don't want your help!
I don't want anyone's help!

950
01:47:37,809 --> 01:47:41,711
- Won't I succeed without your help?
- That's not the case, Rohit.

951
01:47:42,046 --> 01:47:45,345
D'you want to prove that you're so
big that you can make anyone?

952
01:47:45,750 --> 01:47:49,049
I've never thought of it that way,
Rohit. I did it because...

953
01:47:49,387 --> 01:47:52,151
... I know that you can score
better music than those fellows.

954
01:47:52,523 --> 01:47:54,753
That's what I wanted to prove
on my own.

955
01:47:55,426 --> 01:47:57,326
And now, you've spoiled everything.

956
01:47:58,329 --> 01:48:02,163
People will say that I've succeeded
because my wife helped me.

957
01:48:02,533 --> 01:48:04,091
My success will never be mine!

958
01:48:06,537 --> 01:48:10,803
- I can't do it! - Tell Pawan
Malhotra that I won't do this film!

959
01:48:11,109 --> 01:48:13,942
Don't lose your head, Rohit.
Pawan Malhotra liked your music.

960
01:48:14,412 --> 01:48:17,575
That's why he has signed you.
I haven't forced him to.

961
01:48:18,416 --> 01:48:21,408
What does it matter if a few
people tell you a lot of nonsense?

962
01:48:22,487 --> 01:48:26,355
I'm your wife.
If I don't help you, who else will?

963
01:48:27,658 --> 01:48:32,061
I see! So can you walk out on me,
or come to my aid at your sweet will?

964
01:48:32,397 --> 01:48:36,595
You don't want to help me. You just
want to show off your magnanimity.

965
01:48:36,968 --> 01:48:39,368
You want to show me how
small I am, compared to you.

966
01:48:39,437 --> 01:48:41,537
And you want to show your concern
for me though you live apart.

967
01:48:48,012 --> 01:48:53,109
You've always thought ill of me.
You've always got me wrong.

968
01:48:53,151 --> 01:48:55,284
Why must I try to understand
you in the first place?

969
01:48:56,088 --> 01:48:58,722
I don't want to understand you.
Nor do I want to see you ever!

970
01:48:58,723 --> 01:49:00,688
Don't ever try to meet me again!

971
01:49:02,460 --> 01:49:06,294
Stop! Rohit!

972
01:49:07,598 --> 01:49:10,089
- Don't step inside this house ever
again! - Listen to me! Please!

973
01:49:10,501 --> 01:49:13,937
Come to your senses!

974
01:49:15,753 --> 01:49:20,155
I already know why you
argued with me at the party.

975
01:49:20,356 --> 01:49:23,358
She intends to start over
with that man again.

976
01:49:23,759 --> 01:49:27,160
It took only a few minutes with him
to want to ruin everything again.

977
01:49:27,460 --> 01:49:30,662
Don't ever think about it.
Do not think I'll allow it. I won't.

978
01:49:30,762 --> 01:49:34,160
What's going on in this girl's head?

979
01:49:34,458 --> 01:49:38,459
Leave her alone. She must
be tired. Let's go. - No!

980
01:49:39,459 --> 01:49:43,159
I want to hear from her mouth that
she'll never see him again.

981
01:49:59,917 --> 01:50:00,849
How did all this come here?

982
01:50:01,719 --> 01:50:04,688
Look, Daddy! My birthday
presents! Mummy sent these over.

983
01:50:07,592 --> 01:50:11,619
This is a military jeep. It turns
around whenever it collides.

984
01:50:13,498 --> 01:50:15,864
Look! Here's a remote control car.

985
01:50:20,171 --> 01:50:23,197
Why can't we live in
Mummy's house?

986
01:50:26,611 --> 01:50:31,446
- Don't you like this house? - This
home is fine, but... - What of it?

987
01:50:32,049 --> 01:50:34,449
But her house is so big...
and it's so nice.

988
01:50:34,919 --> 01:50:38,912
She has 3 TV sets. We don't
have a single one.

989
01:50:46,397 --> 01:50:47,989
What did Mummy tell you at
this party yesterday?

990
01:50:48,833 --> 01:50:54,032
- She said that she loves me very
much. - What did you tell her?

991
01:50:55,439 --> 01:50:58,272
That she's the best
Mummy on earth.

992
01:51:01,145 --> 01:51:03,841
So now you want to live with
Mummy, do you?

993
01:51:09,787 --> 01:51:12,221
- I'm asking you something.
- Do you know something?

994
01:51:12,657 --> 01:51:15,785
Mummy is going to buy
the battery-operated car for me.

995
01:51:16,494 --> 01:51:20,191
-Did you ask her for it?
-No, I just told her that I like it.

996
01:51:20,765 --> 01:51:23,199
She said that she'd buy it for me.

997
01:51:23,634 --> 01:51:26,227
Why did you have to ask her for it?
I was supposed to buy it for you.

998
01:51:27,138 --> 01:51:32,269
- You haven't got it yet.
- But l was to get it for your birthday.

999
01:51:33,211 --> 01:51:35,679
- And now, my birthday is gone.
- All right. I know that.

1000
01:51:36,314 --> 01:51:42,150
I'll get you that car today.

1001
01:51:43,387 --> 01:51:46,823
Understood? I'll get
it today! For you.

1002
01:51:48,025 --> 01:51:51,051
My car is coming today!

1003
01:52:02,406 --> 01:52:08,675
- How much does that car cost?
- 5000 Rupees. - 5000?! - Yes.

1004
01:52:09,046 --> 01:52:12,573
- It's a bit too much for that car.
- Fixed price. Take it or leave it.

1005
01:52:12,984 --> 01:52:15,714
- An advance of 5000 Rupees?!
- I need the money, Sir.

1006
01:52:16,454 --> 01:52:21,289
So you need all of 5000 Rupees!
D'you hear that, Mr. Godwill?

1007
01:52:22,627 --> 01:52:24,857
You may deduct a thousand rupees
every month out of my salary.

1008
01:52:25,229 --> 01:52:28,426
- lt'd be adjusted within 5 months.
- Will you be here for 5 months?

1009
01:52:29,267 --> 01:52:32,498
Seems like you've got a chance
to sing in some third rate film.

1010
01:52:32,870 --> 01:52:35,361
- And now, you're looking for chance
to give me the slip. - No, Sir.

1011
01:52:35,873 --> 01:52:38,808
That isn't the case at all!
I've forgotten these dreams.

1012
01:52:39,844 --> 01:52:43,712
The only person I have to
myself is my 6 year old son.

1013
01:52:45,283 --> 01:52:49,515
Yesterday was his birthday.
And I had promised him a gift.

1014
01:52:50,354 --> 01:52:54,051
A gift... worth 5000 bucks!

1015
01:52:56,093 --> 01:53:00,257
D'you hear that. Mr. Godwill?! I've
never given a single gift to my son.

1016
01:53:00,598 --> 01:53:03,465
And my good man wants to give a
gift worth 5000 bucks to his son!

1017
01:53:06,470 --> 01:53:12,932
You've spun a good spiel. But, I'm
not one to be taken in my your story.

1018
01:53:13,311 --> 01:53:15,973
- Please try to understand...- Don't
waste my time. And back to work!

1019
01:53:18,983 --> 01:53:23,079
Let's get working. We don't have
a circus happening here, do we?

1020
01:53:25,256 --> 01:53:27,519
- So you won't let me have the
money will you? - Not at all.

1021
01:53:30,094 --> 01:53:34,121
What are you doing?! I'll call
the police! Stop him, Godwill!

1022
01:53:34,765 --> 01:53:36,164
What hooliganism is this?

1023
01:53:36,834 --> 01:53:40,270
Put it down on my account.

1024
01:53:42,073 --> 01:53:43,233
Stop him!

1025
01:53:46,077 --> 01:53:47,101
Catch him!

1026
01:53:59,724 --> 01:54:02,454
Snatch the money from him!

1027
01:54:24,482 --> 01:54:28,009
Know something, aunt Farida? Daddy
is getting me a battery-powered car.

1028
01:54:28,686 --> 01:54:32,315
ls that so?
That's good news, I say.

1029
01:54:32,723 --> 01:54:36,318
- It's getting late. Time to have
dinner. - I won't eat now.

1030
01:54:36,660 --> 01:54:39,390
- I'll eat when Daddy comes home.
- No knowing when he'll return.

1031
01:54:39,564 --> 01:54:41,397
I must go home and get my
kids to do their homework.

1032
01:54:41,566 --> 01:54:44,360
- Go on... eat your dinner quickly.
- No. I won't eat now.

1033
01:54:46,103 --> 01:54:49,334
Very well. I'm leaving the food
here. Eat it when you feel hungry.

1034
01:55:42,460 --> 01:55:48,660
When did you return?
I didn't even get to know!

1035
01:55:54,004 --> 01:55:56,234
Where's the car, Daddy?

1036
01:55:58,576 --> 01:56:02,842
- Why haven't you eaten yet?
- I was waiting for you.

1037
01:56:04,348 --> 01:56:08,114
You mustn't stay awake so late.
I don't like this at all.

1038
01:56:08,919 --> 01:56:12,912
I was waiting so we
could eat together.

1039
01:56:37,348 --> 01:56:46,086
- What's happened, Daddy? - I lost
my son. I have lost. - Don't cry.

1040
01:56:47,157 --> 01:56:52,390
- Please don't cry, Daddy.
- My son asked me for only one thing.

1041
01:56:53,230 --> 01:56:59,794
And I couldn't get it for him.
This is the worst defeat in my life.

1042
01:57:00,871 --> 01:57:04,932
I don't want that car, Daddy.
Really... I don't want it.

1043
01:57:24,194 --> 01:57:29,188
Here... I have some money.
And I'm going to get more.

1044
01:57:29,733 --> 01:57:33,829
And I'm going to get
that car for you.

1045
01:57:39,977 --> 01:57:43,378
But, please stop
drinking, Daddy. Please.

1046
01:57:46,984 --> 01:57:53,548
I'll get that car for you, Sonu.
I will.

1047
01:58:24,888 --> 01:58:27,584
- Mr. Pawan Malhotra has summoned
me here. - Please follow me.

1048
01:58:35,699 --> 01:58:38,259
Please forgive me, Rohit. I've had
you summoned here using the alias.

1049
01:58:40,771 --> 01:58:41,897
Else, you wouldn't have come.

1050
01:58:43,173 --> 01:58:47,200
- I want to discuss something.
- ls anything worth discussing?

1051
01:58:48,212 --> 01:58:50,646
Please sit down, Rohit.

1052
01:58:56,987 --> 01:59:00,445
You had told me something the other
day. All I want to know is whether...

1053
01:59:01,925 --> 01:59:06,624
... it is your final decision.
- Why?

1054
01:59:07,665 --> 01:59:13,331
- Are you still firm about not
meeting me ever again? - Absolutely.

1055
01:59:16,306 --> 01:59:21,369
- ln that ease, I want my son.
- What was it you said?!

1056
01:59:22,379 --> 01:59:26,839
- I want Sonu to live with me.
- You want Sonu! lncredible!

1057
01:59:27,317 --> 01:59:31,185
How could you even think of it?
You left him when he needed you.

1058
01:59:31,689 --> 01:59:34,055
- D'you want me to... - You haven't
seen him in a year and a half.

1059
01:59:34,525 --> 01:59:37,892
You haven't even asked if he's dead
or alive. And now you want him!

1060
01:59:38,328 --> 01:59:42,492
-Sonu needs me. He'll be happy with
me. - And, isn't he happy with me?

1061
01:59:43,467 --> 01:59:47,494
Now wait a minute! D'you mean to
say that I can't keep him happy?

1062
01:59:47,905 --> 01:59:53,741
- I didn't say so. - D'you think you
can give him more happiness...

1063
01:59:54,111 --> 01:59:58,241
... because you're wealthy? - Please
don't shout, Rohit.- Why mustn't l!

1064
01:59:58,549 --> 02:00:03,509
- I'm his mother. And you can't deny
my right. - Neither can you mine!

1065
02:00:03,987 --> 02:00:07,150
I'm his father.
And he stays with me.

1066
02:00:10,294 --> 02:00:12,854
I'd even go to court to get Sonu.

1067
02:00:25,309 --> 02:00:27,607
Well, how do I play that?
Just like Daddy, don't l?

1068
02:00:36,987 --> 02:00:39,512
I'm sorry for having
touched the piano, Daddy.

1069
02:00:51,034 --> 02:00:54,128
ln terms of this notice,
Ms. Kiran seeks a divorce from you.

1070
02:00:54,938 --> 02:00:57,498
And, she wants that the child
be placed in her custody.

1071
02:01:00,444 --> 02:01:07,907
- All I want is my son. - I'll tell
you something before I take the case.

1072
02:01:08,352 --> 02:01:11,947
ln such cases, the decision
generally favors the mother.

1073
02:01:12,389 --> 02:01:14,550
I have been parenting him
for nearly two years now.

1074
02:01:14,825 --> 02:01:17,885
- She had abandoned the child.
- Yet, Ms. Kiran remains the mother.

1075
02:01:18,395 --> 02:01:22,161
Besides, she's a successful woman.
You don't have a job. That's worse.

1076
02:01:28,333 --> 02:01:34,843
You'd have to pay for court fees and
mine to the extent of 50 or 60,000.

1077
02:01:35,512 --> 02:01:38,777
That's irrespective of whether you
win or lose. D'you have the money?

1078
02:01:39,583 --> 02:01:47,046
- Yes. Please prepare the brief.
- Very well.

1079
02:01:47,624 --> 02:01:50,593
You may come here on Wednesday at
10 am. We'll discuss the case.

1080
02:01:51,295 --> 02:01:55,527
- Please bring 20,000 towards
expenses in advance - All right.

1081
02:02:06,777 --> 02:02:11,146
-I can pay 15,000 for all these
instruments.- 15000 only! How come?!

1082
02:02:11,515 --> 02:02:14,973
The piano is worth at least 20,000.
I'd bought it for 30,000.

1083
02:02:15,886 --> 02:02:18,411
I should get at least 40,000
for all the instruments.

1084
02:02:18,789 --> 02:02:21,690
This is business for me. I should
be able to earn a bit out of this.

1085
02:02:23,594 --> 02:02:29,897
- Well, give me at least 25,000.
- I can't pay more than 15,000.

1086
02:02:30,234 --> 02:02:33,067
- Very well, you may leave.
- You seem to be cross with me, Sir.

1087
02:02:33,437 --> 02:02:36,964
- We don't want to sell. Now, please
leave.- It's yours, do as you please.

1088
02:02:37,407 --> 02:02:39,170
- Please leave.
- Excuse me, gentleman.

1089
02:02:39,643 --> 02:02:41,474
What a waste of time!
Why did they call me at all?

1090
02:02:43,881 --> 02:02:47,180
Have you gone out of your mind?
Can a junk dealer appreciate these?

1091
02:02:48,352 --> 02:02:52,516
You're worrying for nothing. Sell
my furniture to raise the money.

1092
02:02:53,423 --> 02:02:59,658
No. You've already
done so much for me.

1093
02:03:02,099 --> 02:03:04,693
- I'll sell my songs.
- Sell your songs?!

1094
02:03:04,968 --> 02:03:06,993
- To whom?
- To Amar Kaushik.

1095
02:03:07,704 --> 02:03:09,262
You've really gone
out of your mind.

1096
02:03:11,275 --> 02:03:14,574
- He's willing to pay me 1000 for
every song. - Who gets the credit?

1097
02:03:15,379 --> 02:03:19,281
- They get the credits.
- You mustn't do such a thing.

1098
02:03:20,817 --> 02:03:25,720
These are fruits of your labor.
They're your hopes, your dreams.

1099
02:03:26,056 --> 02:03:28,286
How can you give that
away to someone?

1100
02:03:30,127 --> 02:03:34,928
Your songs are beautiful, Rohit.
You must get credit for these songs.

1101
02:03:37,167 --> 02:03:40,762
That's what I thought too.
I thought my songs were beautiful.

1102
02:03:41,171 --> 02:03:45,301
But, I've tried for so many years.
And, no one seems to like them.

1103
02:03:45,742 --> 02:03:48,040
And, at long last, I think
I have been entirely wrong.

1104
02:03:48,112 --> 02:03:50,437
- My songs might really be worthless.
- I don't agree to that.

1105
02:03:51,048 --> 02:03:57,715
-You're making a big mistake, Rohit.
- I may be. But, if in exchange...

1106
02:03:57,988 --> 02:04:03,187
... for these, I can have Sonu,
then these songs are priceless.

1107
02:04:05,329 --> 02:04:08,628
Else, these are no more than
scribbling on paper.

1108
02:04:33,150 --> 02:04:36,450
<i>Why did you break my heart?</i>

1109
02:04:37,150 --> 02:04:41,450
<i>Why did we fall in love?</i>

1110
02:04:42,150 --> 02:04:47,450
<i>Why did you go away?
Away... away...</i>

1111
02:04:48,150 --> 02:04:51,450
<i>Why did you steal my heart?</i>

1112
02:04:52,150 --> 02:04:56,450
<i>If you wanted to break it.</i>

1113
02:04:57,150 --> 02:05:00,450
<i>Why did you fall in love with me?</i>

1114
02:05:01,150 --> 02:05:05,450
<i>If you wanted
to turn away from me.</i>

1115
02:05:23,150 --> 02:05:26,450
<i>Why did you break my heart?</i>

1116
02:05:28,150 --> 02:05:30,450
<i>Why did we fall in love?</i>

1117
02:05:32,150 --> 02:05:37,450
<i>Why did you go away?
Away... away...</i>

1118
02:05:56,150 --> 02:05:59,450
<i>You taught my heart how to beat.</i>

1119
02:06:00,150 --> 02:06:04,450
<i>You taught my heart
how to writhe in pain.</i>

1120
02:06:05,150 --> 02:06:08,450
<i>There were hidden
tears in my eyes.</i>

1121
02:06:09,150 --> 02:06:13,450
<i>But you taught them
how to brim over.</i>

1122
02:06:20,150 --> 02:06:23,450
<i>Why did you settle
into my heart?</i>

1123
02:06:24,150 --> 02:06:27,450
<i>If you just wanted
to toy with my affections.</i>

1124
02:06:28,150 --> 02:06:32,450
<i>Why did you fall in love with me?</i>

1125
02:06:33,150 --> 02:06:36,450
<i>If you wanted
to turn away from me.</i>

1126
02:06:37,150 --> 02:06:41,450
<i>Why did you steal my heart?</i>

1127
02:07:18,250 --> 02:07:22,550
<i>Whenever our gazes met...</i>

1128
02:07:23,250 --> 02:07:27,390
<i>I felt as if my heart
was on fire.</i>

1129
02:07:27,400 --> 02:07:31,600
<i>As if smoke was coming
out from my breaths.</i>

1130
02:07:31,700 --> 02:07:37,550
<i>I was not able to
live and neither die.</i>

1131
02:07:43,250 --> 02:07:46,550
<i>Why did you start a fire?</i>

1132
02:07:47,250 --> 02:07:50,550
<i>If you wanted to leave
without putting it out.</i>

1133
02:07:51,250 --> 02:07:55,550
<i>Why did you fall in love with me?</i>

1134
02:07:55,950 --> 02:07:59,550
<i>If you wanted
to turn away from me.</i>

1135
02:08:01,031 --> 02:08:04,057
The filmfare award for the Best
music director, this year for...

1136
02:08:04,434 --> 02:08:10,771
... the song DlL MERA CHURAYA
KYON goes to Amar Kaushik.

1137
02:09:04,761 --> 02:09:08,253
Mr. Rohit Kumar's attorney
has sent me this letter today.

1138
02:09:09,165 --> 02:09:13,829
He has agreed
to divorce Ms. Kiran.

1139
02:09:14,337 --> 02:09:18,205
But he has refused the prayer to
place Ms. Kiran's son Sunil Kumar...

1140
02:09:18,441 --> 02:09:22,241
... under her custody. The case
therefore rests upon the contention...

1141
02:09:22,612 --> 02:09:29,211
... as to who may have custody of
the child. Before arguing the case...

1142
02:09:29,552 --> 02:09:32,783
-... I'll present some witnesses.
- This lawyer is a tough one.

1143
02:09:34,190 --> 02:09:37,284
I shall speak the truth, and
nothing but the truth.

1144
02:09:37,861 --> 02:09:42,696
Can you tell the court something
about your daughter, Mrs. Ramdayal?

1145
02:09:43,500 --> 02:09:48,995
My daughter is a simple girl, and
has all the qualities of a girl...

1146
02:09:49,406 --> 02:09:53,240
... who has had a respectable
upbringing. She's an obedient girl.

1147
02:09:53,710 --> 02:09:57,146
Why then, did she marry Rohit
Kumar against your wishes?

1148
02:09:58,415 --> 02:10:04,376
That's the only mistake she has
committed in all her life.

1149
02:10:04,754 --> 02:10:07,154
And, she's still suffering for
her mistake.

1150
02:10:09,225 --> 02:10:13,958
This man had treated her so cruelly
that she was forced to leave his...

1151
02:10:14,264 --> 02:10:21,033
... house at midnight. - Thank you
Mrs. Ramdayal. You may step down.

1152
02:10:21,971 --> 02:10:25,338
Can you tell the court about Rohit
Kumar's character, Mr. Ramdayal?

1153
02:10:26,209 --> 02:10:29,178
What can I say about a man who
has no character?

1154
02:10:29,512 --> 02:10:35,348
He's a scoundrel; and he's wayward.
You mustn't consider his appearance.

1155
02:10:35,885 --> 02:10:38,581
He inveigled my daughter using
those looks, and with his words.

1156
02:10:38,788 --> 02:10:41,447
- Really?! - He claimed to be
a singer of great caliber.

1157
02:10:41,493 --> 02:10:43,823
And he said that he was going to
become a famous music director.

1158
02:10:43,961 --> 02:10:47,658
He's still where he was.
And look at my daughter!

1159
02:10:48,231 --> 02:10:50,665
She came out, and now, she's so
successful. And we don't want...

1160
02:10:50,667 --> 02:10:52,762
... Sonu to live with him, because
the boy will turn wayward.

1161
02:10:58,408 --> 02:11:02,105
Has Rohit Kumar ever shied away
from fulfilling his responsibilities?

1162
02:11:02,479 --> 02:11:05,414
- No. - Has he ever tried
to shirk responsibility? - No.

1163
02:11:05,782 --> 02:11:10,810
- Has he been negligent towards his
son? - Never. ln fact, he spends...

1164
02:11:11,154 --> 02:11:14,954
... most of his time with his son.
He plays with the boy; amuses him;...

1165
02:11:15,291 --> 02:11:20,888
... reads stories to him and takes
him outdoors. Sunil is his very life.

1166
02:11:24,367 --> 02:11:28,770
I've seen very few fathers who would
do as much for their children.

1167
02:11:30,607 --> 02:11:32,541
Thank you very much, Mrs. Farida.

1168
02:11:38,581 --> 02:11:44,349
- For how many years have you known
Mrs. Kiran? - Some 7 years now.

1169
02:11:44,921 --> 02:11:50,791
Has Ms. Kiran ever told you
about her personal life?

1170
02:11:51,528 --> 02:11:55,794
Questions about Ms. Kiran's personal
life may be addressed to her only.

1171
02:11:57,834 --> 02:12:02,828
- Did she tell you anything about
her personal life. - Yes. - What?

1172
02:12:06,443 --> 02:12:11,574
- She was unhappy.
- With whom was she unhappy?

1173
02:12:12,382 --> 02:12:16,751
- She was unhappy about Rohit.
- Did Ms. Kiran ever tell you...

1174
02:12:17,153 --> 02:12:20,884
... that Rohit Kumar doesn't
care about his son at all?

1175
02:12:27,430 --> 02:12:29,864
Please reply, Ms. Farida.
I haven't yet heard you.

1176
02:12:31,835 --> 02:12:34,736
-Yes. But, that had happened before
Kiran left. - Maybe. But he...

1177
02:12:35,071 --> 02:12:39,405
...didn't care about his son at all.
Now, Ms. Farida, can you tell me...

1178
02:12:39,909 --> 02:12:46,678
...if you ever advised Ms. Kiran
to break away? - No. I did not.

1179
02:12:49,619 --> 02:12:53,146
3 days before she walked out,
did you not tell her that:...

1180
02:12:53,723 --> 02:12:59,154
''If you are so unhappy, it'd
be better for you to leave''?

1181
02:12:59,696 --> 02:13:02,631
Yes. But I never thought that she'd
really do something like that.

1182
02:13:02,999 --> 02:13:08,762
''If you are so unhappy, it'd be
better for you to leave Rohit''

1183
02:13:09,405 --> 02:13:13,466
Kiran was a good friend. And, I was
concerned about her. I still am.

1184
02:13:14,177 --> 02:13:17,374
- And whatever I told her...
- Was born out of your feeling that...

1185
02:13:17,847 --> 02:13:22,079
... had Kiran lived on with Rohit,
she would've gone mad or could've...

1186
02:13:22,452 --> 02:13:27,151
... had a nervous breakdown, or she
may have even been driven to suicide.

1187
02:13:27,423 --> 02:13:32,690
-But l... -D'you want an innocent
child to live with such a man!

1188
02:13:36,499 --> 02:13:40,060
You're making a big mistake, Kiran.
Rohit has changed completely.

1189
02:13:41,504 --> 02:13:44,200
He is no more what he used to be.
Listen to me, Kiran. Please!

1190
02:13:45,208 --> 02:13:51,078
Don't take Sonu away from Rohit.
He needs Sunil. Without him...

1191
02:13:52,181 --> 02:13:53,671
Please don't do this to him.

1192
02:13:54,717 --> 02:13:57,311
If you do not step down, it will be
regarded as a contempt of this court.

1193
02:14:03,760 --> 02:14:06,187
I can't quite understand how you're
going about this case, Mr. Bhatija.

1194
02:14:06,263 --> 02:14:08,788
At this rate, we're going to lose.
... out of the way, please.

1195
02:14:09,332 --> 02:14:11,732
Our witnesses are saying the truth.
And her lawyer is twisting facts.

1196
02:14:12,035 --> 02:14:14,526
D'you want me to tell lies too?
Must I stoop to Bhojwani's level?

1197
02:14:14,871 --> 02:14:21,800
D'you want me to raise a stink
over Ms. Kiran's personal life?

1198
02:14:22,412 --> 02:14:26,041
Am I to prove that she's deranged?
Must I accuse her of adultery?

1199
02:14:26,316 --> 02:14:29,149
- But that isn't true!
- Are you concerned about the truth?

1200
02:14:29,419 --> 02:14:31,717
Or, do you want your son? Tell me.
I'll handle the case accordingly.

1201
02:14:32,055 --> 02:14:34,580
I can present false witnesses as he
does. Do you want me to do that?

1202
02:14:36,459 --> 02:14:39,917
No. Do it honestly.

1203
02:14:46,803 --> 02:14:53,140
Look at her now. She has done well
for herself. She's the ideal woman.

1204
02:15:01,718 --> 02:15:05,882
My next witness is
Mr. Moolchand Gangar.

1205
02:15:10,259 --> 02:15:12,693
- Where did he transpire from?
- I have no idea.

1206
02:15:13,463 --> 02:15:15,795
- Who is he?
- The grocer in my neighborhood.

1207
02:15:16,766 --> 02:15:19,291
- We don't get along too well.
- You haven't told me about him.

1208
02:15:21,604 --> 02:15:25,131
- ls your shop located under
Rohit Kumar's residence? - Exactly.

1209
02:15:25,675 --> 02:15:29,167
- ln that case, you might be knowing
Rohit well. - Very well indeed.

1210
02:15:29,746 --> 02:15:34,206
- I've heard that he buys groceries
from your shop on credit. - Always.

1211
02:15:34,651 --> 02:15:38,246
- He might also be settling your
dues. - No. - Doesn't he?!

1212
02:15:38,721 --> 02:15:41,087
Why then do you still let him
enjoy your credit?

1213
02:15:41,524 --> 02:15:44,789
I allow credits to everyone.
You buy from me and you get credit.

1214
02:15:46,029 --> 02:15:49,590
Did you threaten to lodge a
complaint with the police, when...

1215
02:15:49,899 --> 02:15:52,697
... he had gotten drunk and
beaten you up?

1216
02:15:57,674 --> 02:16:02,976
If I told tales about your wife,
you would've bashed are up too.

1217
02:16:03,379 --> 02:16:05,711
Does it mean that you aren't
a good man?

1218
02:16:06,115 --> 02:16:09,607
It's not a question of being good or
bad. It's more a matter of intent.

1219
02:16:10,186 --> 02:16:14,486
- Now, did he pay you up after
the incident? - No, he didn't.

1220
02:16:14,857 --> 02:16:17,451
Now how does a man run his
household under the circumstances?

1221
02:16:18,027 --> 02:16:20,825
- How can such a person look after
his son? - You mean his son, Sunil?

1222
02:16:21,164 --> 02:16:24,861
- Yes. - He'd give his life for
Sunil. He loves his son very much.

1223
02:16:25,401 --> 02:16:28,427
He loves his son more than
I can ever love my son.

1224
02:16:28,838 --> 02:16:34,606
Love can't satiate hunger. And what
can one who has wrecked his home...

1225
02:16:34,944 --> 02:16:38,744
... provide for his son? - Rohit
Kumar has not wrecked his own family.

1226
02:16:39,048 --> 02:16:43,144
It's she... that woman sitting over
there? She has wrecked the family!

1227
02:16:44,654 --> 02:16:47,384
Please answer questions put to you.
Do not try to give a verdict.

1228
02:16:47,757 --> 02:16:51,853
Forgive me if I have erred. This is
my first ever appearance in court.

1229
02:16:52,261 --> 02:16:55,560
-I came here because he summoned me.
-You may leave now.

1230
02:16:55,898 --> 02:16:59,231
What you say is true. I've hated
Rohit Kumar for not repaying me.

1231
02:16:59,569 --> 02:17:01,002
I've even quarreled with him
for my money.

1232
02:17:01,637 --> 02:17:05,004
But my money isn't the bone of
contention. This is about his son.

1233
02:17:05,374 --> 02:17:11,006
You asked me what he'd do for his
son. Well, he has sold himself!

1234
02:17:11,314 --> 02:17:15,183
It might be easy for Ms. Kiran to
foot the bill for this lawsuit.

1235
02:17:15,218 --> 02:17:17,115
She's a famous heroine.
And she has loads of money.

1236
02:17:17,153 --> 02:17:22,686
But, it wasn't easy for Rohit.
Do you know what he did for his son?

1237
02:17:23,126 --> 02:17:28,496
He sold his life's savings...
his music... to Amar Kaushik.

1238
02:17:29,265 --> 02:17:31,756
They are now taking credit
for his music.

1239
02:17:36,072 --> 02:17:40,441
-Rohit Kumar must've told you that.
-No he didn't. But I know better.

1240
02:17:40,710 --> 02:17:44,069
I've heard all his songs so often,
it's still coming out of my ears.

1241
02:17:44,180 --> 02:17:49,247
The song ''RAJ A KO RANl SE
PYAR HO GAYA''... it's Rohit's.

1242
02:17:50,419 --> 02:17:53,877
I'm telling you the truth! The song
wasn't written by Amar Kaushik.

1243
02:18:00,296 --> 02:18:06,360
- Do you love your son?
- Yes. I love him dearly.

1244
02:18:06,803 --> 02:18:08,703
Why did you leave him?

1245
02:18:09,372 --> 02:18:16,011
He used to think that
I'll remain a failure.

1246
02:18:17,712 --> 02:18:19,473
It ruined my confidence.

1247
02:18:21,717 --> 02:18:27,121
I became fatalistic about
my failures.

1248
02:18:28,324 --> 02:18:33,057
I was confused, and I started
losing my confidence.

1249
02:18:34,597 --> 02:18:39,933
I felt stifled and confused.
I was scared. And I left my home.

1250
02:18:41,771 --> 02:18:48,431
Then, I'd thought it better
for Sunil's sake

1251
02:18:50,332 --> 02:18:52,543
not to take him along.

1252
02:18:52,615 --> 02:18:56,578
Why then do you seek custody of
your son now?

1253
02:18:57,720 --> 02:19:03,047
I know I had deserted him.

1254
02:19:05,048 --> 02:19:11,088
I can never forgive myself
for the mistake.

1255
02:19:12,668 --> 02:19:20,268
But, the situation has changed.
And, I am confident of myself.

1256
02:19:22,278 --> 02:19:30,151
I can look after Sonu very well.
After all I reared him for 5 years.

1257
02:19:30,920 --> 02:19:34,913
Must my child be taken away from me
because I've been away for 2 years?

1258
02:19:36,392 --> 02:19:39,934
He needs me now.

1259
02:19:43,735 --> 02:19:48,293
But I don't say that
he doesn't need his father.

1260
02:19:48,838 --> 02:19:53,901
But, he's still a child. He needs a
mother more than he needs a father.

1261
02:19:55,177 --> 02:19:58,112
And, I'm his mother.

1262
02:20:02,518 --> 02:20:05,043
I'm his mother!

1263
02:20:17,767 --> 02:20:20,235
You've spent nearly 6 years
with your husband.

1264
02:20:21,070 --> 02:20:24,801
- Has he ever manhandled you?
- No. He hasn't.

1265
02:20:25,308 --> 02:20:26,866
- Did he use abusive language?
- No.

1266
02:20:27,310 --> 02:20:30,609
- Has he ever ill-treated your son?
- No.

1267
02:20:31,347 --> 02:20:33,941
- Do you regard your husband
to be a drunkard? - No.

1268
02:20:34,550 --> 02:20:38,042
Has he ever had relations with other
women...in the nature of infidelity?

1269
02:20:38,487 --> 02:20:45,916
- No. - Then, the reason for your
desertion becomes amply clear.

1270
02:20:46,996 --> 02:20:53,925
With whom did you have the longest
lasting relationship before marriage?

1271
02:20:55,438 --> 02:21:00,137
- With my parents. - And you spent
some 22 years with them. - Yes.

1272
02:21:00,576 --> 02:21:03,545
But, you married Rohit Kumar
against their wishes. Right?

1273
02:21:03,946 --> 02:21:05,811
Yes. That's because I loved Rohit.

1274
02:21:06,315 --> 02:21:11,651
With whom, apart your parents have
you shared the longest relationship?

1275
02:21:12,688 --> 02:21:18,058
- With my son Sunil, I think.
- You spent 5 years with him.

1276
02:21:18,161 --> 02:21:19,826
And you've met him only
once afterwards!

1277
02:21:20,129 --> 02:21:23,959
Now consider your husband.
Don't you think you've shared a...

1278
02:21:24,001 --> 02:21:25,268
... very long relationship with him?

1279
02:21:27,303 --> 02:21:28,902
I didn't hear you, Ms. Kiran.

1280
02:21:29,705 --> 02:21:34,733
- Yes. - And how many years in
all, prior to your marriage...

1281
02:21:35,011 --> 02:21:37,172
... and afterwards have you shared
this relationship with him?

1282
02:21:38,714 --> 02:21:43,651
- Nearly 7 years. - 7 years!
Which means that you have failed...

1283
02:21:44,020 --> 02:21:47,251
...to sustain a relationship by
marriage, a social institution...

1284
02:21:47,690 --> 02:21:52,957
... that is held holy and of
irrevocable bondage in our culture!

1285
02:21:55,831 --> 02:21:59,323
- Please state your reply, Ms.Kiran.
- Tell us, Ms.Kiran...

1286
02:21:59,635 --> 02:22:02,661
D'you agree that you've failed
to sustain the relationship.

1287
02:22:03,873 --> 02:22:08,003
- No, I didn't fail. - Didn't you?!
Would you rate this as a success?

1288
02:22:08,644 --> 02:22:11,738
- Your marriage is on the rocks.
- We have failed each other.

1289
02:22:12,481 --> 02:22:15,211
Not ''both of us'', Ms.Kiran.
It's you. You have failed!

1290
02:22:15,418 --> 02:22:21,414
You walked out on your husband.
He didn't. You failed the relationship.

1291
02:22:24,560 --> 02:22:28,724
- It's the marriage which failed.
- Not the marriage. You failed!

1292
02:22:29,098 --> 02:22:32,124
You've failed to sustain the most
precious relationship of your life.

1293
02:22:33,469 --> 02:22:36,199
ls that true? Or, isn't it?

1294
02:22:45,915 --> 02:22:50,113
- Say it aloud. I didn't hear you.
ls it true? Or, isn't it? - Yes.

1295
02:22:51,787 --> 02:22:54,017
She walked out on her
parents after 22 years.

1296
02:22:54,623 --> 02:22:57,717
She walked out on
her husband for 7 years.

1297
02:22:58,360 --> 02:23:03,764
What guarantee that she won't desert
her child after another 2 or 3 years?

1298
02:23:32,595 --> 02:23:34,324
D'you think that your
case stands weakened now?

1299
02:23:34,730 --> 02:23:36,859
You haven't lost a single suit
till date, Mr. Bhojwani.

1300
02:23:36,966 --> 02:23:40,299
- But it seems that you're going to
lose this one.- No comments please.

1301
02:23:43,372 --> 02:23:51,837
Generally, It's the woman who is
favored in disputes like this.

1302
02:23:53,315 --> 02:23:56,307
That's because she's
a woman and a mother.

1303
02:23:57,586 --> 02:24:02,353
But presently, the questions
revolve around the child.

1304
02:24:03,859 --> 02:24:08,922
As I understand, this Court will
decide in the child's interest...

1305
02:24:09,265 --> 02:24:11,358
... about what's good for Sunil.

1306
02:24:13,736 --> 02:24:17,172
I've been looking after
him for nearly 2 years now.

1307
02:24:18,240 --> 02:24:22,506
I've learnt something.
And, I have understood much.

1308
02:24:23,812 --> 02:24:29,751
And slowly, I've understood
what it takes to be a good father.

1309
02:24:31,620 --> 02:24:35,750
It takes patience. One needs to
spend a lot of time with the child.

1310
02:24:37,293 --> 02:24:39,625
For hours, I've heard
him talk of strange fantasies.

1311
02:24:40,462 --> 02:24:42,828
I'd get tired of listening to him.
But, I'd go on listening despite.

1312
02:24:43,432 --> 02:24:46,026
One must reply to a thousand
questions he has to ask.

1313
02:24:46,368 --> 02:24:49,098
One must be there with him whenever
need be, so he might not feel lonely.

1314
02:24:51,440 --> 02:24:57,572
To do all that, one must love.

1315
02:25:00,149 --> 02:25:09,683
And I don't know where it's written
that a woman can love more than a man.

1316
02:25:12,595 --> 02:25:17,328
Must a mother always love
the child more than the father?

1317
02:25:27,009 --> 02:25:31,810
I do not say that the child
cannot have a better upbringing.

1318
02:25:32,748 --> 02:25:35,182
I've always tried my best.

1319
02:25:37,353 --> 02:25:43,485
Sometimes I'd scold him and he'd
go to bed with a heavy heart.

1320
02:25:45,628 --> 02:25:51,396
Up next morning, we'd have breakfast
together and we'd laugh and talk.

1321
02:25:52,501 --> 02:25:53,798
It was all as if
nothing had happened.

1322
02:25:55,404 --> 02:25:59,500
Later, I'd drop him to school.
And while returning from school...

1323
02:26:00,042 --> 02:26:03,341
...he would tell me about what
had happened all day in school.

1324
02:26:03,646 --> 02:26:08,015
We used to dine together. And
afterwards I'd tell him stories.

1325
02:26:16,492 --> 02:26:23,898
We've created a world for ourselves.
And it took a lot of love to do that.

1326
02:26:25,668 --> 02:26:30,696
If this is destroyed,
we can never build it again.

1327
02:26:38,047 --> 02:26:41,847
Don't do this, Kiran.

1328
02:26:43,552 --> 02:26:48,615
Please don't do this to me again.

1329
02:26:59,968 --> 02:27:08,967
You've told the court that it must
decide in the interest of your son.

1330
02:27:09,845 --> 02:27:10,277
Yes.

1331
02:27:11,447 --> 02:27:15,941
Did you work at the Copper Chimney
restaurant when you met Ms.Kiran?

1332
02:27:16,285 --> 02:27:18,378
- Yes,
- How much salary did you draw then?

1333
02:27:18,787 --> 02:27:20,220
3000 Rupees a month.

1334
02:27:23,659 --> 02:27:26,184
But, you were dismissed from the
job, weren't you?

1335
02:27:26,528 --> 02:27:30,589
I wasn't dismissed. I left that
job of my own volition.

1336
02:27:31,066 --> 02:27:33,193
You left the job! And I thought
that people take on...

1337
02:27:33,535 --> 02:27:36,003
... greater responsibilities after
marriage! - I wanted to rise in life.

1338
02:27:36,472 --> 02:27:40,340
- I wanted to become a successful
singer. - You must've received...

1339
02:27:40,743 --> 02:27:45,112
-.. several offers for singing.- l
did get an offer from Amar Kaushik.

1340
02:27:46,014 --> 02:27:50,246
From Amar Kaushik! Lovely! But
I don't think you have sung in...

1341
02:27:50,786 --> 02:27:55,120
-... any of his films. Or, have
you? - I had dropped the film.

1342
02:27:55,657 --> 02:28:01,994
-Left that too! Why? -Differences
had cropped up between us.

1343
02:28:02,731 --> 02:28:05,291
I see... differences!
And what did you do afterwards?

1344
02:28:05,968 --> 02:28:09,734
- I went back to the earlier job.
- At Copper Chimney? - Yes.

1345
02:28:10,305 --> 02:28:12,637
And how much salary
were you paid?

1346
02:28:16,478 --> 02:28:19,845
I didn't hear you, Mr. Rohit.
How much salary were you paid?

1347
02:28:20,682 --> 02:28:25,483
- 2500 rupees. - 2500?!
Down from 3000 to 2500!

1348
02:28:27,423 --> 02:28:33,851
You're the first person ever to
climb down the ladder to success.

1349
02:28:37,366 --> 02:28:41,029
And I do not think it to be
in your son's interest.

1350
02:28:42,404 --> 02:28:52,375
On September 13, you tried to rob
5000 rupees from the cashier.

1351
02:28:52,948 --> 02:28:56,606
No. I didn't try to rob.
I was asking for a loan.

1352
02:28:57,019 --> 02:29:01,053
You tried to take the money forcibly.
And when waiters in the restaurant...

1353
02:29:01,157 --> 02:29:03,349
... tried to apprehend you,
you fought with them physically.

1354
02:29:04,159 --> 02:29:06,252
I was merely taking a loan.
And I had intended to repay it.

1355
02:29:06,595 --> 02:29:10,895
Not only fisticuffs. Furniture was
broken and the restaurant losses.

1356
02:29:11,567 --> 02:29:16,504
For the crime, Mr. Rohit Kumar had
spend some time in a police-lockup.

1357
02:29:16,639 --> 02:29:18,702
- ls it so, or, isn't it?
- Why don't you try to understand?

1358
02:29:18,774 --> 02:29:21,406
Please reply to my question in the
affirmative or the negative.

1359
02:29:22,010 --> 02:29:24,535
I'm trying to give a reply. And l
can't do that in a mere ''yes'' or ''no''.

1360
02:29:25,180 --> 02:29:27,774
I was taking an advance. It was
to be deducted form my salary.

1361
02:29:29,084 --> 02:29:32,019
My son had asked for gift on his
birthday. And, I promised the gift.

1362
02:29:32,588 --> 02:29:35,523
Stop shouting! Else, this court
holds you for contempt.

1363
02:29:40,329 --> 02:29:43,162
Were you confined in the police
lock up, or, weren't you?

1364
02:29:45,534 --> 02:29:47,729
- Yes. I was confined.
- Good.

1365
02:29:48,103 --> 02:29:54,906
- Now, do you consider yourself to
be a responsible father? - Yes.

1366
02:29:55,677 --> 02:30:04,346
Was your son was about to lose an
eye because you were irresponsible?

1367
02:30:05,754 --> 02:30:11,158
- Was your son Sunil about to lose
an eye? - He was playing in the park.

1368
02:30:11,493 --> 02:30:14,326
- And he fell down. - He fell
down because you were careless!

1369
02:30:14,663 --> 02:30:19,123
- And he was about to lose on eye!
- It was an accident.

1370
02:30:19,468 --> 02:30:22,437
- It could've happened to anyone.
- Didn't you tell Ms.Kiran that he...

1371
02:30:23,505 --> 02:30:25,234
...fell down because
you were careless...

1372
02:30:25,674 --> 02:30:28,268
... and that he was
about to lose an eye?

1373
02:30:31,513 --> 02:30:33,777
Tell us, Mr. Rohit, is it true?
Or, isn't it?

1374
02:30:39,521 --> 02:30:46,518
-Yes. -Do you concede that your son
could've lost an eye for your fault?

1375
02:30:47,896 --> 02:30:50,296
Yes.

1376
02:31:14,089 --> 02:31:22,428
I had no idea that my lawyer would
drag that into the court.

1377
02:31:25,334 --> 02:31:27,529
He had asked me
a lot of question.

1378
02:31:28,937 --> 02:31:30,666
I had merely
answered his questions.

1379
02:31:32,941 --> 02:31:38,379
I know you aren't at fault. Please
believe me. I didn't do it willingly.

1380
02:31:47,889 --> 02:31:51,825
After hearing the depositors made
by witnesses, this court has decided...

1381
02:31:52,194 --> 02:31:55,652
... that the child Sunil Kumar be
placed under Mrs. Kiran's custody.

1382
02:32:34,202 --> 02:32:40,766
Vacations start from today.
It's a month long vacation!

1383
02:32:41,276 --> 02:32:44,268
We'll go to Matheran during
the vacation, won't we?

1384
02:32:45,280 --> 02:32:49,410
-Would you like an ice-cream?
-No. I want an ice-candy. -Come on.

1385
02:32:51,486 --> 02:32:53,818
Do you know something. Daddy?
All the kids in my class are going...

1386
02:32:54,056 --> 02:32:56,519
... to Simla on a school trip.
But, I'm not going with them.

1387
02:32:56,558 --> 02:33:01,552
I'll go to Matheran with you. We'll
have lots of fun out there, won't we?

1388
02:33:05,867 --> 02:33:10,270
We'll fly kites over there. And l
will carry the cricket kit with me too.

1389
02:33:45,574 --> 02:33:50,773
I want to tell you something.

1390
02:34:03,959 --> 02:34:06,519
This is a present from me.
It's a seasoned ball.

1391
02:34:07,395 --> 02:34:10,159
Do come over to play cricket.
We'll have a match.

1392
02:34:10,866 --> 02:34:15,963
Oh yes. You'll play for my team.
And we'll beat the grocer's team.

1393
02:34:17,239 --> 02:34:20,504
- Mr. Ramdayal called up to say
that the car is coming. - I see.

1394
02:34:20,876 --> 02:34:22,238
Carry the luggage down.

1395
02:34:23,011 --> 02:34:23,875
Let's go downstairs.

1396
02:34:38,994 --> 02:34:44,830
Don't cry, Sonu. Come on. You'll
enjoy yourself at Mummy's house.

1397
02:34:45,634 --> 02:34:47,534
You'll have lots
of toys over there.

1398
02:34:48,370 --> 02:34:50,270
And I'll come down
to see you too.

1399
02:34:56,444 --> 02:35:00,676
- Take him down, Farida. I'll be
with you in sometime. - Very well.

1400
02:35:06,988 --> 02:35:08,148
Where's your bat, Sunil?

1401
02:35:09,558 --> 02:35:12,254
Where's your bat?... He must've
forgotten it. I'll fetch it.

1402
02:35:12,661 --> 02:35:14,128
Come along, son.

1403
02:36:15,190 --> 02:36:16,320
Sonu has gone downstairs.

1404
02:36:18,059 --> 02:36:19,754
- I want to tell you something,
Rohit. - What?

1405
02:36:25,567 --> 02:36:27,865
This is Sonu's bat.
He forgot to take it.

1406
02:36:29,371 --> 02:36:32,101
I bought a full cricket
kit yesterday.

1407
02:36:32,874 --> 02:36:34,808
Why?! lsn't this bat
good for him anymore?

1408
02:36:35,410 --> 02:36:40,712
No. It's just that I remembered
that Sonu is fond of cricket.

1409
02:36:41,449 --> 02:36:44,907
Not only that. I've bought him
all the toys he could ever want.

1410
02:36:48,957 --> 02:36:52,654
I've made him a room that
looks just like the one here.

1411
02:36:53,528 --> 02:36:56,053
The same bed; a small table;
and a similar cupboard.

1412
02:36:56,998 --> 02:37:00,161
And I've painted the walls
the same shade of color.

1413
02:37:03,505 --> 02:37:10,570
All because I want to
make Sonu feel at home.

1414
02:37:16,418 --> 02:37:22,914
And then I realized that
this is his home.

1415
02:37:25,860 --> 02:37:27,953
A few articles can't make
a home for anyone.

1416
02:37:30,799 --> 02:37:35,429
Sonu stays here.
This is his home.

1417
02:38:03,331 --> 02:38:10,328
Over the past few days, our lives
and our sentiments were laid bare.

1418
02:38:11,706 --> 02:38:15,267
You must've been hurt.
I know that.

1419
02:38:17,045 --> 02:38:21,709
And today I know that nothing
matters more than the relationship.

1420
02:38:24,652 --> 02:38:29,555
I'm sorry for everything
that has happened.

1421
02:38:34,362 --> 02:38:37,354
You're staying here,
Sonu... with your father.

1422
02:38:43,872 --> 02:38:45,100
This is your home.

1423
02:38:58,553 --> 02:39:03,513
This is your home too.

1424
